summaries.short: Season 2 Premiere. A missing shipment of drugs shakes things up; Teresa stays on as Warden; Lorena commands loyalty, respect...and fear.
summaries.full: Season 2 Premiere. Life goes on at Capadocia amid intrigues and gang rivalries, while a shipment of drugs that never reached its destination shapes the outcome of this story. A frustrated Teresa stays on as Warden only to await the release of her daughter. A hardened Lorena commands the loyalty of La Colombiana and the respect and fear of the other inmates.

summaries.short: As the noose starts to tighten, Teresa turns to Lorena for help. Federico suspects that the lost shipment of drugs is in Capadocia.
summaries.full: As the noose starts to tighten, Teresa turns to Lorena for help. Federico suspects that the lost shipment of drugs is in Capadocia and organizes a search inside the prison. Meanwhile, Andrea is victim to a scheme hatched by La Negra. Teresa hires a new psychiatrist at the institution named Valeria, who is disturbed by her own life story.

summaries.short: When the security video falls into the hands of the Governor's enemies, a warrant is issued for Andrea's arrest.
summaries.full: When the security video falls into the hands of the Governor's political enemies, the police issue a warrant for Andrea's arrest. Santiago quits as Governor and a candidate for president. While Teresa gets ready to escape Mexico with her daughter, Andrea turns herself in. After announcing that what she did was a mistake, Andrea is sentenced to prison.

summaries.short: Capadocia is investigated by the Public Prosecutor; new shrink Valeria disturbs the inmates with her resemblance to La Bambi.
summaries.full: Capadocia is under investigation: the Public Prosecutor has to clear up a crime that points in many directions, and affects the ECSO, as well as Teresa and her family. The arrival of Valeria, the new psychiatrist at the prison, is disturbing to the inmates because of her astonishing resemblance to La Bambi.

summaries.short: Andrea is caught vandalizing a jewelry shop with a man, destroying display cases and stealing jewels.
summaries.full: A hooded man and woman carry out acts of vandalism inside a jewelry shop, destroying display cases and stealing jewels. Yet before the two escape the woman reveals her identity to the security camera--it's Andrea. Teresa fights for the release of a group of inmates who have completed their sentencing for their minor crimes.

summaries.short: Victor Hernandez, the deputy prosecutor who is investigating Capadocia, becomes the headache for ECSO, and a plot gets Sandra locked up.
summaries.full: Victor Hernandez, the deputy prosecutor who is investigating Capadocia, becomes the headache for ECSO, and a plot gets Sandra locked up behind bars. Teresa warns Valeria: 'Capadocia is a black hole that devours anything in its grasp.'

summaries.short: Former madame Zaide gets her ex-clients in the higher courts to pull some strings on her behalf and is released.
summaries.full: Zaide gets her ex-clients in the higher courts to pull some strings on her behalf and is released. Sofia's pregnancy forces her husband Joel to steal from his job. He gets caught and Sofia almost kills herself by aborting her unborn child. Lorena realizes that Cristobal and Federico are using the inmates to smuggle their drugs inside the lingerie.
